Heavy rains in the high mountains around Holy Cave in #Amarnath triggered floods in water body and surrounding springs at around 3 PM today. Immediate alert was sounded and more than 4,000 pilgrims were taken out of the area safely till now. Situation is under control.
Shri Amarnathji Yatris laud efforts made by Indian Army in rescuing them to the safer locations on the Yatra tracks in the wake of cloud burst incident near the holy cave shrine. #AmarnathYatra

Most of the yatris who were stranded near Holy cave area due to flash flood last evening have been shifted to Panjtarni. The evacuation continued till 3.38 AM. No yatri is left on the track. About 15,000 people were safely shifted till now : ITBP

In Jammu and Kashmir, a cloud burst occurred last evening near holy Amarnathji shrine inundating the cave. Water came from above and sides of the cave after heavy rains at the upper reaches. The rains are still continuing since last evening.
